\intbl \ql \b Background\b0 \line The Boston City Campus and Business College is registered with the Department of Higher Education and Training as a higher education provider and is accredited to offer higher education programmes by the HEQC.\line \line The Diploma in Public Relations programme was tabled at the Accreditation Committee meeting of 22 and 23 February 2012 and was not accredited for the following reasons\'3A \line \line 1. The design is flawed. There is no coherent structure for the programme. There is no knowledge progression. The first year of a Diploma should provide knowledge for progression in a three-year programme while the related HC should be a stand-alone programme.\line 2. The naming convention for the programme is not correct. The institution has placed this programme under CESM category 4 \'28Marketing\'29 while the programme deals with public relations \'28CESM 5\'29. The placement under CESM 4 is not consonant with the content and outcomes of this programme. The programme appears not to be focused on Public Relations Practice but rather more on Corporate Communication i.e. management and strategy of PR.\line 3. It is not clear how the experiential learning component will be supervised and the institution has not accepted responsibility for the placement of students.\line 4. The institution does not have a clear understanding of the needs of the distance mode of delivery. Materials development is not explicitly catered for in its policies.\line 5. The staff members are not all relevantly qualified and experienced.\line 6. Given that the registrar and the programme coordinator are the same person\'2C it is not clear that there is sufficient academic expertise to provide academic leadership and curriculum development.\line 7. Resource provision in terms of library resources and computer access is insufficient. The student support for distance education mode is inadequate.\line 8. There is no description of the number and types of assessments\'2C whether formative or summative\'2C and there is also no evidence of how the overall outcomes will be assessed.\line \line The institution submitted a representation. \cell \pard 

